/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50523_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50523_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51168_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted from branches")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51168_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</> - Song of the Bossonian Archers.

Carved from a single piece of wood, the hunting bow is used across the world and in hundreds of variants.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51402_ShortDesc", "A composite bow crafted of silk string and branches")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51402_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Kerim Shah had unslung the powerful Turanian bow that killed at five hundred paces, and the Irakzai looked to their own lighter and less lethal bows.</> - The People of the Black Circle

This bow is made in the Hyrkanian style, using different materials to strengthen different areas of the bow and allowing it to be shorter than a longbow. For Hyrkanians, who spend most of their lives shooting from horseback, this is a necessity.

Hyrkanians are widely considered the best archers in the world, raised to the hunt and the art of shooting from horseback. Their bows, however, are not as well made as those of the Shemites, who have spent centuries perfecting the art.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51406_ShortDesc", "A bow forged from an ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51406_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Springing to his feet, he bent his bow powerfully and drove his last shaft point blank at a great hairy shape that soared up at his throat. The arrow was a flying beam of moonlight that flashed onward with but a blur in its course, but the were-beast plunged convulsively in midair and crashed headlong, shot through and through.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Created based on an ancient design found in the Exiled Lands, this bow seems to confuse the eye with its odd, alien curves.

In the thrum of the bowstring, it whispers of gibbering terrors screeching beneath a blood-red moon and the terrified screams of those who flee the merciless hunt.

One who holds this bow too long risks being drawn into its miasma of madness.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54003_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92094_ShortDesc", "This bow has a demonic entity bound to it")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92094_LongDesc", "It is unknown as to which specific demonic entity is bound to this bow, but whichever it is, it hungers for death. A pity, then, that the entity this demon possessed was merely a goat. Otherwise, this weapon could have been quite formidable.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92098_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted from the bones of a winged demon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92098_LongDesc", "This bow is made from the hollow bones of the Nest Mother. Its construction is awkward yet powerful.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92219_ShortDesc", "A composite bow crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92219_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time. 

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92236_ShortDesc", "A composite bow crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92236_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time. 

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53611_ShortDesc", "Arrows with flint heads")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53611_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53652_ShortDesc", "Arrows made with an Abysmal Fang")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53652_LongDesc", "The fangs of the Abysmal Remnant are made of a hardened substance that can withstand strong acid. They are also razor sharp.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53656_ShortDesc", "Arrows with heads forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53656_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Now arrows fly between the hosts like stinging clouds that hide the sun.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

There is very little that can defend a target from such an exquisitely made arrow. But star metal is precious and rare, and not always available.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53654_ShortDesc", "Arrows with hardened steel heads of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53654_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds. Cimmerians use this fine metal to create arrowheads that will put holes straight through the fine and pretty armor of their civilized foes.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53658_ShortDesc", "Arrows crafted from shards of ice infused with the power of Ymir")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53658_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51184_ShortDesc", "Primitive arrows made from bone")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51184_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53615_ShortDesc", "Arrows that release a healing cloud")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53615_LongDesc", "Made somewhat unwieldy by the bag of ground aloe attached to them, these arrows will release a small cloud of healing gas wherever they strike.

This doesn't seem like a practical way to deliver healing in battle, as there is just as much chance of healing foes. But... some people like exotic solutions.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53616_ShortDesc", "An arrow of evil and ancient design")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53616_LongDesc", "Who knows what sorcery is etched upon the head of this ancient arrow? All that is know is that every shot with it weakens an enemy, corrupting their soul and leaving them gasping for relief.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53617_ShortDesc", "An arrow that explodes on impact")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53617_LongDesc", "Only a madman would willingly carry arrows like this into battle. The chance of hitting friends when trying to damage foes, the chance of accidentally ricocheting an arrow back into oneself, and the chance that the arrows will explode in the quiver...
A madman or a berserker, perhaps.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53619_ShortDesc", "A hollowed out arrow filled with a poisonous powder")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53619_LongDesc", "This arrowhead has been hollowed out and filled with a poisonous powder. Designed to split upon impact, the arrow releases a cloud of poisonous spores into the air, damaging any standing within.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53620_ShortDesc", "An arrow containing an oily solution")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53620_LongDesc", "The hollow arrow is filled with a pair of special reactants that mix together on contact with the ground and form an oily pool.\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51529_ShortDesc", "An arrow made in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51529_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51503_ShortDesc", "Arrows tipped with sharp, black glass")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51503_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, these arrows are made of obsidian. They are brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51471_ShortDesc", "An arrow formed from ivory ")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51471_LongDesc", "Like cultures and customs, the value of ivory depends upon the kingdom where it is seen.

In the Hyborian kingdoms, where elephants and other creatures are rare, it is a tangible sign of both wealth and power. In the Black Kingdoms, it is common - few warriors exist in those lands who do not possess an ivory handled dagger or jewelry.

It is a great source of trade between the north and the south - indeed it could be said that ivory is the primary reason that merchants dare make the dangerous journey along the Black Coast to trade for it in Kush.

This ivory arrow, honed to perfection, is excellently balanced and will cause great damage.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54004_ShortDesc", "Arrows crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54004_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50515_ShortDesc", "An ancient weapon found in the Unnamed City")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50515_LongDesc", "Made from the bones and claws of the Winged Death, these arrows cause tremendous damage.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51216_ShortDesc", "Arrows made from the mandibles of a giant spider")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51216_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92099_ShortDesc", "Arrows made from the hollowed bones of a winged demon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92099_LongDesc", "These arrows were not crafted as much as ripped from the dead bodies of the winged Children of Jhil.")
